annotationA: Synapsin (Syn) is a phosphoprotein associated with synaptic vesicles. It interacts with the endocytic scaffolding protein Dap160. Phosphorylation of synapsin at serine 6 is required for associative short-term learning/memory and short-term olfactory habituation. It is important for outgrowth of synaptic boutons at the larval neuromuscular junction
annotationB: Synaptosomal-associated protein 25kDa (Snap25) is a synaptic target SNARE protein and a component of SNARE protein complexes known to function in neurotransmitter release. Snap25 functions in synaptic transmission in larvae and is essential in adults; Belongs to the SNAP-25 family
